window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Battle Mage or Magical Engineer? Like that was even a real question. Battle Mage...</b><b><i>obviously.</i></b></p> <p>Magical Engineers live quiet, boring lives. I crave excitement.</p> <p>And as an agent for the Arcane Mage Intelligence Agency,</p> <p>That’s exactly what I get.</p> <p>It’s a pretty great life. I go on solo missions, kicking ass and taking names, I hook up with men whenever I want to blow off some steam, and I hang out with my family if I’m ever after company.</p> <p>Everything changes when my psycho uncle fails in his attempt to kill my father. Now, I’m in charge of the manhunt against him.</p> <p>I’ll make sure he pays for threatening those I hold dear.</p> <p>The only problem? I’m no longer working solo, and the team I’ve been assigned is a threat to both my sanity and my heart.</p> <p><i>Deadly Illusions</i> is the first book in Arcane Agent, a paranormal reverse harem series. It is a spin-off of the Arcane Mage series, though it can be enjoyed separately.</p> <p><i>Intended for mature listeners due to cursing, violence, and sexual content.</i></p>"; 
